knowledge_graph.title: The Bank Job
knowledge_graph.description: Self-reformed petty criminal Terry Leather (Jason Statham) has become a financially struggling car dealer and settled into a pedestrian London life with his wife and kids, but takes the plunge into big crime when his ex-girlfriend, Martine (Saffron Burrows), turns up with an offer to pull off a lucrative bank heist. After Terry assembles his crew of misfits and begins the operation, he finds that there are other agendas at play, and powerful players who have designs on the vault's contents.… MORE
knowledge_graph.nominations: Edgar Award for Best Motion Picture Screenplay, Satellite Award for Best DVD Extra

critic_reviews.summary: Statham is surely charismatic, but the film is defined by its thinly drawn characters (the stereotypical militant, the hypocritical politicos) and by-the-numbers plot.
Jason Statham stars in this seedy and sordid fictionalization of a real-life 1971 bank robbery in Britain.
Despite a good premise, this is oddly uninvoling - culminating in a real disappointment.
